1
00:00:04,640 --> 00:00:06,520
Dad, play it again.

2
00:00:06,960 --> 00:00:09,960
Tell me, don’t they get tired of hearing
that song over and over and over?

3
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:12,360
And you don’t get tired of watching soccer?
-What are you comparing?

4
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:14,840
What do you care what they listen to?
As long as it’s quiet.

5
00:00:14,920 --> 00:00:16,640
Is this quiet? I can’t
listen to that song anymore.

6
00:00:16,720 --> 00:00:18,960
Then stop it. Let’s see you.
-What do you think, I don’t have the guts?

7
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:20,160
I don’t know.
-I’m stopping it.

8
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:21,240
Stop.

9
00:00:21,320 --> 00:00:24,440
There. I stopped. Girls, I’m sorry
but Dad’s sanity is at stake.

10
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,720
I really hope you understand
but Dad is begging, enough with that song.

11
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:30,960
Oh, it’s quiet.
-Wait.

12
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:33,680
I need to pee.
-I want a little sister too.

13
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:34,880
Play it again.

14
00:00:34,960 --> 00:00:36,440
Got it?
-Yeah.

15
00:00:37,480 --> 00:00:38,400
It’s quiet.

16
00:00:44,080 --> 00:00:46,240
Look at me, look at me. And...

17
00:00:56,880 --> 00:00:57,720
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

18
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:00,240
Shabbat Shalom.
-So, where have you been? I was already worried.

19
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:02,640
Come on, come on, girls, come on.

20
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:04,080
Sit down.
-Shabbat Shalom.

21
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:06,760
Why are the girls half-naked?
-Because it’s hot outside.

22
00:01:07,240 --> 00:01:09,560
But that’s not modest.
-Riki, they’re kids.

23
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:13,720
Okay, okay, why are you getting confused? What did I say?

24
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:15,960
That she dresses her daughters like whores maybe?

25
00:01:16,040 --> 00:01:18,760
Pinchas...
-Meet her, this is...

26
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:21,240
When do we eat? I’m starving. Is there schnitzel?

27
00:01:21,320 --> 00:01:23,120
No, wait, wait, hold on a second, before the schnitzels.

28
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:25,160
I have a surprise.
-Oh no.

29
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:27,400
How nice. Are you pregnant?
-No, no, no.

30
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:28,680
This is the ultrasound video.

31
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:30,080
What do you mean, Dad?
-No, it’s...

32
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:31,000
Why “what do you mean”?

33
00:01:32,520 --> 00:01:34,880
Why did you bring this
when I told you at home not to bring it? Right?

34
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:37,960
So you took advantage of the fact that I have
a small bladder and when I went to the bathroom...

35
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:39,320
Bam!
-Come on, enough. Enough.

36
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:42,320
Come on, Michali, what’s the surprise?
-So, I won the trial.

37
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,440
Wow...
-And I got the video.

38
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:45,600
Great.
-Awesome.

39
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,240
Congratulations.
-Someone filmed me once too.

40
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:49,400
I thought about suing him.
-No, no...

41
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:51,920
No, it’s our wedding video.

42
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,560
Of course, it’s about time. So many weeks of trial...

43
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,920
Okay, so come on, do you want to see it?

44
00:01:56,240 --> 00:01:57,680
When?
-No. Come on, babe, drop it.

45
00:01:57,760 --> 00:01:59,720
I told you at home. People
don’t want to see that right now.

46
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:02,320
Maybe after the food?
-Why? So you can say

47
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:04,720
that your kids are tired and bail?
-No, because I’m a bit hungry.

48
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:07,800
Come on, I’m dying to see it.
I wasn’t at the wedding after all.

49
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:10,360
Just so you know, sit down, people really talked about it

50
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:12,440
that it’s not nice you weren’t at the wedding.

51
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:15,200
I was in the delivery room, Riki.
-I know.

52
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:18,360
I’m just saying people talked.
-Okay, is the movie long?

53
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:19,480
No, it’s only three hours, come on.

54
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:22,160
Come on, babe, why the fuss now? Really.

55
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:25,000
We don’t have to watch everything. Come on, Adam,
talk to them. They’re so heavy. Come on.

56
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:26,520
Sit down, you were on epidural during that time.

57
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:29,280
I need to see it sober.
-What, aren’t you curious to see it?

58
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:31,800
Dude, I watch it a lot.
-You have to! There. For what?

59
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:33,000
Okay, I’m putting it on. I have to see.

60
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:34,440
Just a little.
-Oh, babe.

61
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:36,000
Tasty.
-Really tasty.

62
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:37,360
Really tasty.

63
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:38,400
Get up, get up.

64
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:44,920
It's starting, it's starting, it's starting.
-Oh, Shai, really tasty.

65
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,920
Okay, you’ve met her already. Enough, pest.
-No, but I didn’t say...

66
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:47,920
Tell me, what are you, a kid?

67
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:58,000
"Will you marry me, my love? Be my wife?

68
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:05,240
And give me your hand! I’ll stay by your side."

69
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:06,680
Heartfelt.

70
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:08,040
I'm dying, I can't take it.

71
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:12,200
"Come on, let’s swear by love

72
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:19,640
I’ll give you a ring at the wedding

73
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:25,400
I promise you, my woman

74
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:31,640
I’ll keep you forever like my heart

75
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:39,440
Because without you, my love, I can’t go on

76
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:45,760
So excited about you and don’t know how to ask

77
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:52,640
Will you marry me, my love? Be my wife?

78
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:58,080
And give me your hand and I’ll stay by your side."

79
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:00,800
"I’m dying.
-It’s like a cheesy movie.

80
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:03,320
But what did you expect? You dragged that photographer

81
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,480
to court for five weeks. This is what you got.

82
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:06,920
Mom, I’m dying...

83
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:17,120
Turn off the camera.
-Wait, just a second, babe.

84
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:19,200
I’ll break it for you.
-Babe, stop.

85
00:04:19,279 --> 00:04:22,680
No! Stop. Babe, stop!

86
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:31,920
"Will you marry me, my love? Be my wife?

87
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:35,120
And give me your hand..."

88
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,720
Okay, son, can we stop this now?

89
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:40,680
Do you get it? According to the ruling
they were supposed to give us

90
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:43,720
the wedding video edited properly,
but because of the lawsuit...

91
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:45,840
they included everything unnecessary on purpose.

92
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,760
Michal, if I were you, I’d sue them again.

93
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,800
Let’s go eat.
-Wait, wait, come on, wait.

94
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:53,360
Maybe it gets better later in the wedding.
Just hold on, I want to see.

95
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:55,720
Just because you chose not to be at the wedding

96
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,440
doesn’t mean we all have to suffer.

97
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,120
I didn’t choose, Riki.
I gave birth. It’s not a choice.

98
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:05,360
You knew the wedding date.
You could have had a C-section a week earlier.

99
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:07,840
Mom, enough.
-Okay. What did I say?

100
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:10,840
I’m just saying people do things like that.

101
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,480
Okay, okay, I want to see what they did to me.

102
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:16,000
No, babe, why ruin a wedding
that in your memory was wonderful

103
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:18,640
and had great alcohol?
-Yeah, the slivovitz.

104
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:20,720
Look. The reception.
-I, son, babe.

105
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,680
I want to see that too.

106
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:26,120
Hello. Thank you, thank you very much.

107
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:29,720
Come here. Listen, go sit down.

108
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:31,440
Hello.

109
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:33,360
What was that?

110
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:34,880
No, it was like a jump in the movie.

111
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,840
Suddenly blinked one moment too long.

112
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,600
How many people did she invite?

113
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:42,280
I don’t know half of the friends here.
-Mom, they’re not.

114
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,720
Hey, here are my parents and my sister.
-Hello.

115
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:48,880
Congratulations.
-Good to see you. Congratulations to you too.

116
00:05:48,960 --> 00:05:50,120
Congratulations.

117
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:52,640
Thank you very much, thank you very much.

118
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:55,720
Really, you didn’t have to come. Thank you.

119
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:58,600
Did I tell you?
-She’s laughing.

120
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,960
You see, it’s not even edited. There’s no music.

121
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:05,480
I'm telling you, this is going to end badly.

122
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,320
It's his wedding. I want to know what happened there.

123
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,040
Hey, there you are, babe.

124
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:12,000
Shai..
-Thanks a lot.

125
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:13,760
What a hunk.

126
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:17,480
Shai's parents are already here.
-Congrats to you too, Mom.

127
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:20,760
Oh, thanks, bro. Thanks. Congrats to you too, Ar...

128
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:23,600
People will say she found the perfect time to give birth.

129
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:26,160
Why would they say that?
-Because people talk.

130
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,960
They're filming us.
-It's fine, they'll edit it later.

131
00:06:30,520 --> 00:06:31,880
You, on the other hand, will squeeze that lemon.

132
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:33,760
She's not going to be here for many weeks, right?

133
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:35,720
Move it, you're causing a traffic jam.

134
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,760
You got it.
-Thanks a lot.

135
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:39,000
What did I even say?

136
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:42,720
This movie is not okay.
It takes things out of context.

137
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:45,520
Maybe it's better not to eat.
-Look, here comes Adam.

138
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:49,640
Adam's here. Adam, hello.
-Congrats.

139
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,120
Nice to meet you.
-Hello.

140
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:52,840
Adam.
-Hello.

141
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:55,960
Who was that with you at the wedding?

142
00:06:57,520 --> 00:07:00,160
Just someone. I don't even
remember her name.

143
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:02,720
Not serious.
-Her name is Gabriela.

144
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:05,400
And she was lovely.
-Thanks, Mom.

145
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:09,520
I really thought she was the one for you.
-Thanks, Mom.

146
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:12,040
Lovely.
-Great, thanks.

147
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:16,160
So, did you invite her to the wedding?
-My mom invited her with me.

148
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:17,640
She's the daughter of someone from her kibbutz.

149
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:20,320
I thought you could have given her a chance.

150
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:23,720
The daughter of Tabbabalat, from the first marriage.

151
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:26,480
I... I'm out.
-Okay, quiet, shut up.

152
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:27,720
Here comes the little guy.

153
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,560
Uncle Shmuel.

154
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,920
I put you at the family table.

155
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:37,560
The check box is here.

156
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:39,840
Who just walked by behind?
-Okay. Maybe enough of that?

157
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,840
Enough. I'll buy the raw materials from them,

158
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,560
I'll take it somewhere
they can prepare it properly,

159
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:46,040
logically, and that's it. Come on, shall we eat?

160
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:47,240
Yeah, let's go.
-Let's go.

161
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:51,000
Wasn't that his ex?
-Who? Smadar?

162
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:52,200
No way!
-No chance!

163
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:54,160
You're exaggerating.
-No way.

164
00:07:55,840 --> 00:07:57,520
Shaker.
-Here comes my sister.

165
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,080
Take our picture.

166
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:01,520
Snap it.
-Cheers!

167
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:04,000
What are you doing here?
-Riki told me to come pick up the kids.

168
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:06,400
I'll bring the kids later, after the ceremony.

169
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:09,480
Out.
-Smadar, you're part of the family.

170
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:12,280
I even put you at the family table.

171
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:14,680
It's fine. What, it's Meital's night.
-Michal.

172
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:15,960
Michal.
-Michal.

173
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:18,200
I'm taking the kids and I'm leaving. What...

174
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:19,880
Do me a favor, Smadar, don't let Michal see you

175
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:22,000
because she'll kill me.
-The camera's already turning.

176
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:26,120
Thanks, thanks for coming.

177
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:29,560
Shh_

178
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:33,080
So nice to see you. What are you doing here?

179
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:34,760
What do you mean? It's my brother's wedding.

180
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:37,720
He's marrying my cousin.

181
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:39,240
Is Michal your cousin?
-Nice.

182
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:42,600
How about you? Already in the bathroom?

183
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:46,240
Who's that chubby one?

184
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:49,120
Believe me, I don't even remember
her name.

185
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:52,400
You two look great together.
-No, I'm dying.

186
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:55,440
You know her.
-I think...

187
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:57,360
I think she was with me
in the scouts or something.

188
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:01,440
-Right.

189
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:04,720
Sit down, we don't know her.

190
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:08,240
Hey, here’s my brother.

191
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:10,040
Congratulations.

192
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:13,160
Congratulations.
-Thanks, thanks.

193
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:19,480
And you didn't connect Michal and me?
We have the same last name.

194
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:21,680
The Cohen.
-The Levi.

195
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:24,400
The Levi. Smadar?

196
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:28,080
Hey, congratulations.
-Thanks, thanks.

197
00:09:28,160 --> 00:09:30,480
I just came
to pick up the kids right after the ceremony.

198
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:32,680
The camera keeps spinning over here,

199
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:34,680
I'm passing it to that section.
-Sure.

200
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:14,000
No, I'm dying.
-No, I'm dying.

201
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:16,680
Someone's gonna die here.
-Everyone dies in the end.

202
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:18,600
Yeah? That's a promise, Riki?

203
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:23,080
The music is really loud here.

204
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:25,240
What's that?
-A microphone.

205
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:27,440
Moshe, what's that? Something's moving on my plate.

206
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:29,040
Mom, we have a cockroach.

207
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:31,440
What should I do with it?
-Bless the couple.

208
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:39,320
It's a disaster. Really a disaster.

209
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:41,000
Let the cockroaches bless them.

210
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:44,680
The groom's mom looks like she's stressed out.

211
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:46,760
The food was way better in the army.

212
00:10:56,920 --> 00:10:58,080
There's a clog in the bathroom.

213
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,040
That's why it smells.

214
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:06,520
Do you see the food?
I ate half, didn't eat half.

215
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,920
You really can't chew it.

216
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:14,160
Shai's family finished all the alcohol.

217
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:15,960
No. I'm dying! I'm in hell.

218
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:19,440
Well, babe, you know
we had a terrible ceremony.

219
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:22,200
Terrible isn't even the word.
-I enjoyed it.

220
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:24,120
You were drunk.
-That's why I enjoyed it.

221
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,640
That's not true, it's this garbage,

222
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:27,840
because of the speech he pushed all the bad parts.

223
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:32,320
Michali, I was at your wedding,
and you had a wonderful wedding.

224
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:35,440
Well, maybe we should stop this nightmare and go eat?
-Yeah, let’s go.

225
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:38,240
No, no, no. I want to see
what else happened behind my back.

226
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:40,200
Don't move!
-Babe...

227
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:43,040
You hear me? I'm setting your microphone
for exit number 2 for the ceremony.

228
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:56,120
Why is she here, why?

229
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:58,560
Why? Because you have a crazy mom.

230
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,960
Mom invited her?
-Of course, of course.

231
00:12:01,040 --> 00:12:04,360
She thinks her son will dump
his wife at the wedding and marry her.

232
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:06,880
She put her at the family table.

233
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:09,600
Why did Mom think I would leave
Shani the day I had a girl?

234
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:11,880
Itamar will leave his wife, not you.

235
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:14,120
Ah... so the troublemaker isn't here because of Mom.

236
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:17,440
So listen to this, you won't believe
who Michal's cousin is!

237
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:19,360
What? Itamar? What about Itamar?

238
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:21,640
What’s Mom doing to Itamar? He's getting married today.

239
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:22,800
She's not normal.

240
00:12:23,880 --> 00:12:25,800
Hey, isn't that guy over there filming us?

241
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,600
No, he's filming that girl.

242
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:29,200
Okay, I need more.

243
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:30,640
Bring me some too.
-Sure.

244
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:33,960
Of course I'm not normal. I married him.

245
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:36,120
What do you want, Rivka? You really overdid it.

246
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:41,560
Pinchas, if there's one thing I hate
it's people talking behind my back.

247
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:44,520
If you have something to say, say it to my face.

248
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:47,080
Who are those people sitting over there at that table?

249
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:48,920
I think they're from Michal's side.

250
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:51,840
That's the ugliest group I've ever seen in my life.

251
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:56,800
Well, what was I expecting? Did you see the food?

252
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:00,360
And the rag on Michal's head?

253
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:04,080
What is this awful music?

254
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:07,840
Rivka, try to see the glass half full.

255
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:11,040
I tried, but you drank it.

256
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:15,480
Chill with the drinking, Pinchas.
People are already talking.

257
00:13:15,560 --> 00:13:18,320
Why can't you say one positive thing?

258
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:21,360
One.
-What is it? To bless the couple?

259
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:22,600
Are we starting?

260
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:27,360
Isn't it recording? It was connected to the boom.

261
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:28,560
Oh, okay.
-There, now it's recording.

262
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:29,480
So, let's start.

263
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:34,880
Congratulations to Michal and my Tamari,

264
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:37,760
you have a wonderful wedding.

265
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:41,000
I've never been to one like this.

266
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:43,720
They say, my Tamari,

267
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:46,160
third time's the charm - ice cream.

268
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:47,920
Nonsense, nonsense, I'm just kidding.

269
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,800
Congratulations, congratulations!
-Congratulations! Cheers!

270
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:52,680
Congratulations.
-See? I was positive.

271
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:55,200
Cheers!
-Cheers!

272
00:13:55,280 --> 00:13:57,560
No, I have no words.
-There's always a first time.

273
00:13:57,640 --> 00:14:00,480
Come on, Mom, maybe that's enough?
-What did I say?

274
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:02,600
Okay, enough with this.
It's Friday today. Let's all relax.

275
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:05,040
Yeah, what's up with the food? People are hungry.

276
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:06,640
I don't think I can put anything in my mouth.

277
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:08,280
No, no, let's go eat. We've seen enough.

278
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:10,640
Wait, wait, wait. At least let me see the chuppah.

279
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:18,200
There were other cameras there,
so why are we only seeing this one?

280
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:21,440
What was the lawsuit about anyway?
-Itamar didn't want to pay for the drone camera.

281
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:24,400
And for the entertainment system, which was extra
that they brought on their own.

282
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:25,720
Of course, babe.

283
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:30,520
No, I hate weddings.
-God willing, your turn will come too.

284
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,040
Amen.

285
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:33,480
Not now!
-Not now!

286
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:50,280
It's not what it looks like.

287
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:55,080
Her fork fell. I helped her look for it.

288
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:56,800
That's it.

289
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:58,440
And did you find it?

290
00:14:58,520 --> 00:15:00,160
Because you left without a fork.

291
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:04,840
...will be heard in the cities of Judah
in the streets of Jerusalem,

292
00:15:04,920 --> 00:15:09,520
the voice of joy and the voice of gladness, the voice of the groom and the voice of the bride.

293
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:14,440
I want to understand what I'm seeing.
I'm in labor, screaming in pain,

294
00:15:14,520 --> 00:15:16,000
and you're flirting at a wedding with girls?

295
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:19,240
Not with girls, just with one girl.
-Pinchas, do me a favor.

296
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:21,040
First of all, you were already after giving birth.

297
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:24,240
Secondly, I wasn't flirting. She was flirting with me.

298
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:25,800
What could I do?
-What could you have done?

299
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:27,840
Maybe say no, maybe tell her to stop,

300
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:28,800
maybe tell her you're married,

301
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:31,640
Maybe tell her to go to Adam
because he's free for the ride.

302
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,960
Ouch.
-I told her, go at seven.

303
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:34,920
They just edited that out.

304
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,960
My tongue will stick to my palate if I don't remember you.

305
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:40,960
If I don't raise Jerusalem above my joy.

306
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:44,440
If I don't raise Jerusalem above my joy.

307
00:15:44,920 --> 00:15:47,680
Break the glass.
-Break the glass.

308
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:14,520
Can I?
-What? Is that all I have from the wedding?

309
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:17,920
I had an amazing dress. I was...
don't you dare touch the remote.

310
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:21,400
Itamar, you taught me everything I know.

311
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:26,760
Baby--- you know, and I'm an excellent student.

312
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:28,240
So I wanted to say thank you.

313
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:33,320
To you, and to Michal, congratulations from me, your little brother.

314
00:16:33,880 --> 00:16:37,320
!Hagit here also joins in the thanks.

315
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,760
Call her! Gabriela! She was lovely.

316
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:42,720
Let's pause this movie and go eat.

317
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,520
Yeah, food, right away.
-Come on.

318
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:46,320
You have to try my mom's schnitzel.

319
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:48,320
No schnitzel today. I made shlufas today.

320
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:50,880
Let's watch a bit more.

321
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:55,320
It must be getting better.
-It can't be worse than shlufas.

322
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:05,200
Gorgeous!

323
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:08,200
Gorgeous!

324
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:16,000
Come on, let's go, come on.
-What?

325
00:17:17,319 --> 00:17:19,440
We told Shani we'd be at her place. Let's go.

326
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,839
But Meirav doesn't want to leave yet.

327
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:24,560
Then let Meirav come later.

328
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:34,680
!Turns out it was
worse than Mom's shlufas.

329
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:36,520
I can't believe Smadar was at my wedding.

330
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:38,200
She's family.
-She's his ex-wife.

331
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:41,400
Honey, she just came to pick up the kids.

332
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:43,440
Didn't you notice they disappeared at some point?

333
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:45,920
Well, they got tired of it too.
-You know what bothers me the most?

334
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:49,800
That you all hid her from me. You all made a kabubia.

335
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:51,520
Kabubia? My mom's shlufas are kabubia.

336
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:57,040
Just so you know, there are kids in Africa
who would be happy to get my shlufas.

337
00:17:57,120 --> 00:18:00,480
Of course. It's a tool in a sack.
-Michal, no one tried to hide anything from you.

338
00:18:01,040 --> 00:18:03,800
Yeah, honey. You just didn't notice,
you were drunk.

339
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:06,600
Drunk? I was drunk?
I maybe had two glasses.

340
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:09,480
Two glasses, but test tubes?

341
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:17,600
They had really pretty colors, the test tubes.

342
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:25,880
Okay, I need some air. Sh'.
-I'm coming.

343
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:30,480
Sh', you need to dance more.
You dance really well.

344
00:18:32,960 --> 00:18:34,960
See, honey, I told you
you didn't need to see this.

345
00:18:35,040 --> 00:18:39,320
Sometimes you need to see to believe.
-Well, I see and I don't believe.

346
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,960
But what do you want from me? It wasn't my fault.

347
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:55,200
I just want to remind you she was born 4.750.

348
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:58,840
What does that have to do with anything?
-When you get 4.750 out of your body,

349
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,880
then you'll understand what it has to do with it.
-Come on, sit down, really...

350
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:04,280
What, you realize there was nothing there.
She was drunk and a mess,

351
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:07,240
otherwise she wouldn't have hit on me.
What am I... it's not like I'm Brad Pitt.

352
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:10,120
Yeah, that's true.
-So, all good?

353
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:13,000
Are there more incriminating clips of me in the movie?
-I hope not.

354
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:15,480
I mean, no, none.
-So, all good.

355
00:19:15,560 --> 00:19:17,840
Come on, let's go in before your mom
finds another reason to talk about us.

356
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,680
She doesn't need a reason.
-Yeah, that's true too.

357
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:26,000
You didn't drink anything, huh?

358
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:34,080
Look, this is where you first met Adam.

359
00:19:42,480 --> 00:19:44,040
You're a charmer too.

360
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:57,640
No, that's it. Now I'm totally dead.

361
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:59,880
Is that a threat or a promise?
-Rebecca...

362
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:01,680
What do you want?
-What do I want?

363
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:03,880
At our wedding, you went and kissed your ex?

364
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:06,560
That was a good luck kiss,

365
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:09,080
not a "Hey, let's do this
right here in front of everyone."

366
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:11,000
Oh, thank God.
-Rebecca...

367
00:20:11,080 --> 00:20:13,880
Oh, what did I say?
-I get it, the Rosen men

368
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:16,200
partied at that wedding.
-We were drunk!

369
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:19,200
Now I see why you didn’t want
to watch the wedding video.

370
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:21,760
What are you hinting at?
-I’m not hinting. I’m saying it.

371
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:24,200
Each of you had something to hide. All of you.

372
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:28,360
Shame on you! A wedding is supposed to be a celebration of...

373
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:31,280
happiness, joy, and innocence!

374
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:35,040
Endless love. That’s how
I felt at my wedding.

375
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:36,600
Congratulations, babe.

376
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:40,680
What congratulations? Do you realize
what family I married into?

377
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:45,680
What disgusting people. Itamar's whole side.

378
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:49,760
I’m telling you, they don’t deserve someone like me.

379
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:56,600
You’re on my side, right?
-I think so.

380
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:58,160
Then I love you.

381
00:21:00,080 --> 00:21:03,560
Wow, you look beautiful. Stunning.

382
00:21:09,320 --> 00:21:11,080
So, Liri, you said there’s shlofs?

383
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:13,440
Plenty.
-Shall we do a kiddush?

384
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:14,360
Yeah, let’s go.

385
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:15,640
Let’s go.
-Come on.

386
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:18,200
What is shlofs anyway?
-Shlofs.

387
00:21:18,760 --> 00:21:20,600
You’ve never had shlofs?
-No.

388
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:24,120
Ah... you’re in for a real treat
because it’s like... like klops,

389
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:25,520
just heavier.

390
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:28,360
It’s a big joy!

391
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:32,360
Let me get this straight, is someone making fun of me and my shlofs?

392
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:33,720
No, of course not, Mom.

393
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:36,880
Great, because I made some for all of you to take home.

394
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:40,640
"And there was evening and there was morning, the sixth day

395
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:43,680
and the heavens and the earth and all their hosts

396
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:45,800
Sabri Maranan."
-Cheers!

397
00:21:47,920 --> 00:21:51,720
It was actually nice, even though I usually
don’t like watching wedding movies.

398
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,240
It was fun to know, right?

399
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:56,080
Do you think she’ll put it on YouTube?
-I don’t think so.

400
00:21:57,240 --> 00:22:00,880
So, what do we even do with this thing?
-Put it in the freezer.

401
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:03,320
It’s not coming into my house.
-Then throw it in the trash.

402
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:05,960
No, we don’t throw away food.
-This isn’t food. It’s shlofs.

403
00:22:07,280 --> 00:22:11,720
Fine, stop by the trash can.
-Why is it called shlofs?

404
00:22:12,280 --> 00:22:15,960
It’s called that because of the noise
it makes later in the bathroom.

405
00:22:16,320 --> 00:22:17,400
Of it.
-Pass.

406
00:22:18,560 --> 00:22:21,400
Her name is Gabriela, and she was lovely.

407
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:23,560
Thanks, Mom.

408
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:26,080
Why are you laughing?

409
00:22:27,760 --> 00:22:29,280
I regret it today, Orna.

410
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:31,560
I finish around ten, eleven.

411
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:35,600
What happened?

412
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:41,280
Wasn’t that Smadar? No. What?
-Okay.

413
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:43,440
Exactly.

414
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:47,960
What is this awful music?

415
00:22:48,920 --> 00:22:51,560
Rebecca, try once to see the glass half...

416
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:56,920
It got stuck, the advance got to the throat. Sorry.

417
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:00,400
You two look great together.

418
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:01,200
No, that’s not it.

419
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:02,880
Oh, really?

420
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,640
That she even brings it up at all.

